## Backend-only catalog and rerank

- Catalog source: `frontend/public/data/data.json` imported into SQLite via `python manage.py import_perfumes_from_json --reset`.
- Model: `api.models.Perfume` now includes name_en, name_fa, brand, collection, family, season, character/intensity, notes_top/middle/base, all_notes, tags, images.
- APIs:
  - `GET /api/perfumes/` → DB-backed catalog (ordered by brand/name).
  - `POST /api/recommend/` → baseline matcher (TF-IDF) using DB data.
  - `POST /api/recommend/rerank/` → baseline + OpenAI (timeout/fallback; currently returns baseline if AI is unavailable).
- Env:
  - `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_MODEL` (default gpt-5-nano), `OPENAI_RERANK_TOP_K` (default 30), `OPENAI_RERANK_TIMEOUT_MS` (default 9000).
- Frontend:
  - Do not use local JSON; call backend endpoints directly.
  - Next.js `/api/recommendations` is deprecated and returns 410.
- Notes:
  - Run `python manage.py migrate` before import.
  - IDs in DB match IDs from `data.json`; brands/collections are resolved to names during import.
